cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.IR

The paper primarily focuses on using machine learning techniques to analyze clickstream data in MOOC videos to understand student behavior and predict attrition. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses incorporating diverse perspectives from statistics and information retrieval (cs.IR) to offer a more nuanced view into how MOOCs can be improved. The use of clickstream data also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) to analyze discussion forum interactions. Finally, the paper discusses the application of cognitive psychology (cs.CY) to develop a quantitative information processing index.
